{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1771340602,"nonce":"fvoP5xTxhcvSrAoKnf5Dqa7XDGg=","title":"Admin checkbox for department staffed status is broken","message":"The custom `staffed=` setter in `Department` model compares with `== true` and `== false`, but Rails form params come in as strings (\"0\"/\"1\"). Since \"0\" != false and \"1\" != true in Ruby, the setter silently ignores checkbox values from the edit department form.\n\nThe admin checkbox in `app/views/departments/_form.html.erb` (line 52) can never change the staffed status. It only works through the staff/unstaff controller actions which pass actual boolean values.\n\nFix: either use `ActiveModel::Type::Boolean.new.cast(val)` in the setter, or compare with truthy/falsy values.","files":null}]}